		<summary>
			<description>
				Max is a 6-year-old male castrated Labrador mix that presented to your clinic with a femur
				fracture that you surgically repaired 2 days ago. He recovered well from surgery and has
				been on 1.5x maintenance crystalloid fluids and constant rate infusions of fentanyl (3
				mcg/kg/hr) for analgesia and midazolam (0.2 mg/kg/hr) because he has been anxious. You
				were disconnecting him from his fluids to get him out of his cage for a physical exam and
				accidentally flushed the line containing the fentanyl and midazolam. As soon as you finish
				flushing the line, Max collapses and becomes unresponsive.				
			</description>
			<breed>Labrador Mix</breed>
			<gender>Male</gender>
			<weight>20 kg</weight>
			<symptoms>
				Unresponsive.
			</symptoms>
			<image>fido.jpg</image>
